Installation:

	git clone git://github.com/hogon/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

	ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
	ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

	cd ~/.vim
	git submodule init
	git submodule update
	git submodule foreach git pull origin master

Congratulations your installation is done !


The following is optional.
 Clewn may be helpful if you would like to get GNU Debugger access directly from your Vim.

To install clewn
	vimdir=$HOME/.vim  ./configure  --prefix=$HOME
	make
	from : https://groups.google.com/group/vim_mac/browse_thread/thread/1a7b591e69635357?pli=1
	-I/opt/local/include to Makefile DEFAULT_INCLUDES on line 63
	-L/opt/local/lib to LDFLAGS on line 119
	$ clewn -ga './executable' 
	$ path/to/MacVim.app/Contents/MacOS/Vim -g -nb:localhost:3219
	Use C-n for "next", S for "step", F for "finish" etc,   See ":h clewn" for more info. 

rgb2cterm is helpful is you would like to to have color of the hexadecimal color code.
To install rgb2cterm
	ln -s $HOME/.vim/script/Vim-toCterm/rgb2cterm $HOME/scripts/rgb2cterm
	in scheme source, :so <path to Vim-toCterm>/tocterm.vim
	see https://github.com/shawncplus/Vim-toCterm
